    <note>Shu(4) Zhengqing [18278] Address based on that of son, Changru [18282], although his wife was buried in Dongping, home of father [I read the passage in Liu(2) Qi's funerary inscription for his brother, Shu(4) Duanqing [18279], as follows: "Uncle Zhengqing took the petition of Sengru (not in dataset), son of his youngest brother, Binqing [18281], to (Liu(2) Qi) and requested a funerary inscription"]. The move makes sense since his wife, born Wang, was a Mizhou resident. Lu Dian, WJ, 15.15b-17a (wife, born Wang, who followed the ideal-type pattern and became marriageable through the ceremony of binding up the hair at 15 and married Zhengqing at age twenty. died in 1099 at age 68). CBD, 2, 1068.</note>
